title: Get permission to take a child abroad

heading_context: Get permission to take a child abroad
chunks.html_content: You must get the permission of everyone with parental responsibility for a child or from a court before taking the child abroad.
chunks.plain_content:
Get permission to take a child abroad
You must get the permission of everyone with parental responsibility for a child or from a court before taking the child abroad.

heading_context: Get permission to take a child abroad
chunks.html_content: Taking a child abroad without permission is child abduction.
chunks.plain_content:
Get permission to take a child abroad
Taking a child abroad without permission is child abduction.

heading_context: Get permission to take a child abroad
chunks.html_content: You automatically have parental responsibility if youre the childs mother, but you still need the permission of anyone else with parental responsibility before you take the child abroad.
chunks.plain_content:
Get permission to take a child abroad
You automatically have parental responsibility if youre the childs mother, but you still need the permission of anyone else with parental responsibility before you take the child abroad.

heading_context: Get permission to take a child abroad
chunks.html_content: You can take a child abroad for 28 days without getting permission if a child arrangement order says the child must live with you, unless a court order says you cant.
chunks.plain_content:
Get permission to take a child abroad
You can take a child abroad for 28 days without getting permission if a child arrangement order says the child must live with you, unless a court order says you cant.

heading_context: Get permission to take a child abroad
Get permission from someone with parental responsibility
chunks.html_content:
A letter from the person with parental responsibility for the child is usually enough to show youve got permission to take them abroad.

You might be asked for the letter at a UK or foreign border, or if theres a dispute about taking a child abroad. The letter should include the other persons contact details and details about the trip.

It also helps if youve:

  • evidence of your relationship with the child, eg a birth or adoption certificate
  • a divorce or marriage certificate, if you are a single parent but your family name is different from the childs

heading_context: Get permission to take a child abroad
chunks.html_content:
Youll need to apply to a court for permission to take a child abroad if you havent got permission from the other people with parental responsibility.

You must give details of the trip, eg the date of departure, when and how youre returning, and contact details of people with parental responsibility staying in the UK.

You must give more information if youre taking the child abroad for a longer trip, eg what education the child will get while theyre abroad.

Find a solicitor to get legal advice about permission to take a child abroad.

heading_context: Get permission to take a child abroad
Check the age limit in the country youre travelling to
chunks.html_content: You need to contact the embassy or consular office of the country you are travelling to for information about the age limit up to which a person is considered a child.
